  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.view.Window.Callback, com.yandex.money.api.processes.ExternalPaymentProcess.ParameterProvider, com.yandex.money.api.processes.IPaymentProcess.ParameterProvider

    public final class PaymentActivity
extends android.app.Activity
implements com.yandex.money.api.processes.ExternalPaymentProcess.ParameterProvider

    Main activity for a payment process. It guides a user through all payment steps and returns information whether payment was successful or not.

    To explicitly start this activity you may want to use getBuilder(Context) method to create an Intent object, that can be passed to Activity.startActivity(Intent) or Activity.startActivityForResult(Intent, int) methods. See the description of allowed parameters in PaymentActivity.PaymentParamsBuilder and PaymentActivity.Builder interfaces.

    If the activity was started using Activity.startActivityForResult(Intent, int) method, then it will return result of a payment to a calling activity. If payment was successful, then result code will be Activity.RESULT_OK and EXTRA_INVOICE_ID will be present in returned data object. If payment was canceled by a user or rejected by payment system, then result code Activity.RESULT_CANCELED will be returned.
